&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 2 years of experience in software engineering.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have built, deployed, and maintained production services and understand service-oriented architecture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You write high quality, well tested code.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You can author technical design documents and break down features into discrete tasks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You actively use modern tooling (including AI-assisted development) to ship faster and learn new domains quickly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are passionate about building an open financial system that brings the world together.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice to haves:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with security tooling or security-adjacent engineering (e.g., SLSA, Sigstore, artifact scanning, SBOM).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with Artifactory, Xray, or similar supply chain security platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Golang, Docker, Kubernetes, Postgres, MongoDB, gRPC.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with cloud infrastructure (AWS or GCP).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have worked at a company during a period of rapid growth.&lt;/li&gt;
